OL,6,FNevertheless, average bills remain
OL,7,Fconsiderably lower than during the
OL,8,Fpeak of the energy crisis, which was
OL,9,Ffuelled by Russia's invasion of
OL,10,FUkraine in February 2022, driving up
OL,11,Fcosts in an already-turbulent energy
OL,12,Fmarket.
OL,14,FThe expected #1,714 a year would be
OL,15,F#120 less than the price cap in
OL,16,FOctober last year, when it was #1,834.
