OL,3,CWarnings Welsh homes will go cold this
OL,4,Cwinter as price cap increases by 10%
OL,6,FThe Bevan Foundation's Head of Policy
OL,7,Ffor Poverty, Dr Steffan Evans said
OL,8,F"people who should be getting help
OL,9,Ffrom energy suppliers are sometimes
OL,10,Fbeing left short and are forced to
OL,11,Fturn for help elsewhere.
OL,13,F"This is putting extra pressure on
OL,14,Fservices such as foodbanks and advice
OL,15,Fworkers which are already stretched.
OL,16,FAs we head into what is likely to be
OL,17,Fanother difficult winter, energy
OL,18,Fsuppliers must up their game to make
OL,19,Fsure that their support schemes reach
OL,20,Feveryone who needs them."
